values:
okay, so before I moved I got a postcard that was addressed to Kragen, my cat, from his vet reminding me that he was due for a couple shots.  I decided to wait until I moved to make the appointment.  Today I recieved a postcard addressed to me and it cracked me the hell up!  This is what it says...

"Dear Mary,
     Just in case Kragen forgot/misplaced/ate or has hidden the reminder we sent, our records show he is due for the following treatments or examinations.  Please give us a call for an appointment.  Remind Kragen that all kitties who visit recieve a present of special catnip!!!"

Today I subbed for the high school behavioral program and had a REALLY good day.  Sometimes the students can be triggered by the smallest of changes and having a sub isn't that small of a change.  Overall it was great and even the paraeducators were surprised on how well the kids behaved all day.  

I always tend to look at the walls and see what is up because some teachers have the coolest things posted in their classrooms.  The following is something this particular teacher has posted on the outside of her office door.  It's called The Invitation by Oriah I'll put it under a cut to save space.  It really spoke to me today so I had to share it with all my friends here.

<lj-cut text="The Invitation">

It doesn't interest me what you do for a living.
I want to know what you ache for and
If you dare to dream of meeting your heart's longing.

It doesn't interest me how old you are.
I want to know if you will risk looking lik a fool 
for love
for your dream
for the adventure of being alive.

It doesn't interest me what planets are squaring your moon...
I want to know if you have touched the center of your own sorrow
If you have been opened by life's betrayals
or have become shrivelled and closed from fear of further pain.

I want to know if you can sit with pain
mine or your own without moving to hide it
or fade it 
or fix it.

I want to know if you caan be with joy
mine or your own
If you can dance with wildness
and let exstasy fill you to the tips of your fingers and toes
without cautioning to be careful, be realistic
remember the limitations of being human.

It doesn't interest me if the story you are telling me is true.
I want to know if you can disappoint another to be true to yourself.
If you can bear the accusation of betrayal and not betray your own soul.
If you can be faithless and therefore trustworthy.

I want to know if you can see beauty even when it is not pretty every day.
And if you can source your own life from it's presence.

I want to know if you can live with failure 
yours and mine
and still stand at the edge of the lake and shout to the silver of the full moon,
"YES."

It doesn't interest me to know where you live or how much money you have.
I want to know if you can get up after the night of grief and despair
weary and bruised to the bone and do what needs to be done
to feed the children.

It doesn't interest me who you know or how you came to be here.
I want t oknow if you will stand in the center of the fire with me
and not shrink back.

It doesn't interest me where or what or with whom you have studied.
I want to know what sustains you from the inside when all else falls away.

I want to know if you can be alone with yourself
and if you truily like the company you keep in the empty moments.

~Oriah Mountain Dreamer, from the book The Invitiation </lj-cut>

CENTRAL WASHINGTON FOOTBALL ROCKS!  

Seriously...the game was a BLAST!  We totally dominated the game and the ending score was 37-17!!!!  I wore my Western shirt that says (on the front) Western, we know you suck... (back) BUT do you spit or swallow?!?!?  I'm butt crusty tired so I'm off to bed.  Just wanted to most that CWU rocks my socks!

My dad has started to paint the wall of my sister's baby's nursery.  He is using the Finding Nemo theme.  It looks sooooo good!  It is crazy what kind of artist my dad is!  He isn't even half way finished with the wall yet as the picture takes up the whole wall or at least over 50% of the wall.  I think it adds a cool personal touch to the baby's room.  My sister and brother-n-law is having my brother-n-law's aunt make the bumbers for the crib out of specific fabric to match the wall and all.  Anyways here is a pic of the progress to this point.
Like I promised...here are a couple of pictures of my knee.  The bruising is actually blood pooling in the side of my knee from where the bone broke.  They are nasty so take that as a warning...

I wanted to get an update out to all you readers.  I'm still around I have just been way to busy and druged up to post an entry.  Last Monday I had a biking accident where I have a small fracture in my knee and tore some tendons away from the bone.  I'm doing better now.  I'm walking on it but I have a HUGE brace and at night still take some pain medicine.  My knee is nasty looking.  It's sooooooooooo black and blue it isn't even funny.  Aight well I'm off to go elevate my leg.

Tonight after I was done tutoring I put my bike on my bike rack, on my car, picked up my Dad and his bike and went out to Lake Padden.  It was so nice.  It was around 7:30pm so it was cooling off as it has been high 80's low 90's here and riding on the trail around the lake was awesome.  I like spending time with my Dad and I love Mt. Biking so this was awesome.  We only went around the lake once but it's about 2.5-3miles.  My dad may be 58 years old but he still can Mt. Bike and we both just had an ubber of a good time.

Sometimes working for my mother SUCKS!  I went to work on Saturday and was told that I had to dress up like Twisty (Auntie Anne's Mascot) and be in Old Navy's Fall Fashion Show (yes you all may laugh now)!  I not only had to dress up as Twisty but I had to carry a lunch sake one show and a backpack the next and actually walk the runway.  It was better than being WITH Twisty as no one knew who I was.  But here is something to make you all laugh.

Okay, so I know I put up a post with a couple pictures of Sadie who is my friend's dog, but my dad took better pictures when I took her to my grandparents house for a bar-b-q.  She is an American Pitbull and one of the sweetest dogs I have ever known.  I took her back to my friend today and I miss her!  The cats are glad she's gone, except for Kragen who loved her, but it's quiet again on the front. So again, I present Miss Sadie May....

On Thursday I had the vascular tumor on my finger removed.  Oh my goodness did it hurt like a bitch.  I almost passed out.  I had to change the bandage last night and I almost passed out because of the pain.  I never want to go through this again.

Okay, so yesterday I went to get the oil changed in my sister's car with her and ended up buying a NEW car.  Well...it's a 2002, but hella new to me.  It's a Jetta.  The color is green and I love it.  It still has Warranty on it so it makes me feel better about that.  I am a first car buyer so my payments are a lil' high, but you know that's what it takes to get the credit.  I bring home the new car today.  I ran out of time before I had to tutor and I needed to take my sound system out of my old car.  They paid 3000.00 for my old clunker.  Suckers!  Anyways.  I'll try to take some pictures and all.
Okay so I KNOW I'm Whoring out my cat, but he's just so damn CUTE!

Okay, Okay...so I finally changed where I keep my photos so hopefully photobucket will allow them to be seen on LJ.  I'm soooooo sorry for the problems before.  They totally ticked me off.  Anyways, like I said before...Kragen is mine so I'm partial, but Gorch (AKA Gorchy) is so darn cute that I included a couple of him (He's the black one).  Hope you enjoy.

I actually had a life last night!  I met L at Starbucks for coffee and enjoyed myself.  I miss that girl because I rarely get to see her!  It was good to get away from practicum and school work and just hang out!  Thanks for a good night L!

Okay this is one time that I'm soooooooo happy to be at the public schools because they are CANCELLED!  Yep Mare woke up and got ready and then 6:50am got a call that school is cancelled.  I still have my evening class (if it doesn't get cancelled) but for now I can sit on my ass and not do anything.  I won't complain...i just got a 4 day weekend!

Independant. You have an air of power around

negative, and hard to relate to, but you give
off a relaxed image despite being insecure -
and secretly many people long to be like you,
not knowing how deep the Winter season really
is. Well done... You're the most inspirational of
seasons :)

Well, it has been awhile since I have updated and that's not because nothing has been going on, it is just that I have been ubberly busy with summer classes.  I must say that while summer classes are kicking my ass I am having such a great time.  First off I have an amazing statistic professor.  I mean she just utterly rocks!  Today she was talking about saying one thing and writing another and if we catch her doing it to stop her and she was like, "Yeah I'm sure I have a bizarre case of statistical tourettes!"  She like is the most down to earth, intelligent woman around this campus on statistical stuff!  

The excitement for this weekend was that I got stung by a bee!  Yes Mary the person allergic to everything is ALSO allergic to BEES!  Lucky for me it was on my arm so I didn't have to go to the hospital and I had gotten benedryl into my system within 7 minutes of getting stung and FINALLY today (3 days AFTER the fact) my arm is getting back to normal size!  I went to the dr's and got some meds for it that won't knock me on my ass like benedryl does and I got a perscriptionprescriptionHATE bees and here in E-burg we have TONS of them.

Next week should be interesting as I'm going to be having my two lil' cousins over for the ENTIRE week!  Yes I'll be responsible for a 13 year old and an 11 year old.  I have classes in the morning but we are planning fun things for the evening.  Like riding our bikes to get ice cream and a day in Seattle at the zoo!  I really do enjoy my lil' cousins so it should be a grand old time!

By the way messages for individuals...Tia when do you leave for Ireland??? Lauren...just wishing you a digity dank day!

"If you don't want what I want, please try not to tell me that my want is wrong.
Or if my beliefs are different from your's, at least pause before you set out to correct them.
Or if my emotion seems less or more intense  than your's, given the same circumstances, try not to ask me to feel other than I do.
Or if I act, or fail to act, in the manner of your design for action, please let me be.
I do not for the moment at least as you to understand me.  That will come only when you are willing to give up trying to change me into a copy of you.
If you allow me any of my own wants, or emotions, or beliefs, or actions then you open yourself up to the possibility that some day theseways of mine might not seem so wrong, and might finally appear as right - for me.
To put up with me is the first step to understanding me.
Not that you embrace my wayz as right for you, but that you are no longer irritated or disappointed with me for seeming waywardness.
And one day, perhaps in trying to understand me, you might come to prize my differences and far from seeking to change me, might perserve and even cherish those differences.  
I may be your spouse, your parent, your offspring, your friend, your colleague.  But whatever our relation, this I know:
You and I are fundamentally different and both of us have to march to our own drummer." ~Unknown~

The above quote states how I feel.  I'm so tired of people judging me and trying to change me.  I just want to be left the way I am.  I just want to be me and I'm sorry if that is not what you want from me, but last time I checked it wasn't your choice.  I want to be encouraged for the good I do and not torn down because I'm not the mirror image of someone else!  I just want to be accepted and NOT judged..guess that's a lot to ask though...
